&gt; query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is
&gt; submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed
&gt; accordingly.
&gt; 
&gt; An attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the
&gt; SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the
&gt; input filePath; this input is then read by the downloadFile method at
&gt; **(@RequestParam String filePath)** of src\main\java\com\sample\controller\S3Controller.java. This input then
&gt; flows through the code, into a query and to the database server -
&gt; without sanitization. This may enable an SQL Injection attack.

