How to pass Checkmarx?

answers.body_markdown:
I know that this is late, but a simpler way would be to do it like this (assuming processing-java is in your path).&lt;br&gt;
```processing-java --sketch=$PWD --run```&lt;br&gt;
and add it to an alias:&lt;br&gt;
```alias pjava=&#39;processing-java --sketch=$PWD --run```

`scala.Seq` is a type alias for `scala.collection.Seq` (this [changed](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/69591709/cats-auto-derived-with-seq) in Scala 2.13)

https://github.com/scala/scala/blob/v2.11.12/src/library/scala/package.scala#L45

```
type Seq[+A] = scala.collection.Seq[A]
